    "summary": "Since ever I am interested in agriculture and agricultural techniques in general and I have the chance to work in this area every day. I like team working, having multiple contacts in and out the company. I like to lead projects courageously and to make every effort for seeing them achieved with success. I am very careful of keeping a global view about the projects which we implement by our partners.\n\nAs a technical and sales representative I gained enough knowledge and methodology to analyze and understand any markets. How to position a product, to launch it, to develop it, to animate it, is my daily work for my customer portfolio. The customer relationship is at the heart of my concerns and of my work. Each year within a team, I managed the technical development of 2 to 3 projects in launching process: protocols thinking, field trials setting-up, synthesis and data recovery towards our business partners for commercial referencing.\n\nAREAS OF EXPERTISE:\nMarketing \u2013 Sales management \u2013 Technical and business support to sales team\n  - Marketing strategy : segmentation and positioning\n  - Marketing plan\n  - Negotiation and Sales\n  - Customer Market Analysis : analysis of customers, competitors, target market\n  - Action plan to launch new technical innovations\n  - Product training to my customer portfolio to improve sales.\n  - Product plan communication : E-mailing, technical sheet\n\nProduct Development\n  - Technical knowledge in plant protection (Grapevine, Fruit growing and Field crops) and crop production.\n  - Field trials: writing protocols, monitoring, scoring, analyzing results and communication\n  - Agronomical skills\n\nSPECIAL SKILLS:\nComputer skills:\n  - MS Office package (English versions)\n  - Software's and languages : Visual Basic, R, ARM (Synthesis of agronomical trials)\nMobility: 100%\nHome-Office for more than 5 years",
